titleofevent: Seeds of Disruption: How Food Technology Will Save the Planet with Bruce Friedrich, hostorganizationoryourname: Penn Animal Advocacy and Penn Animal Law Project, date: 4/19/2017, starttime: 5:00:00 PM, endtime: 7:00:00 PM, location: Hall of Flags, Houston Hall, typeofevent: Vegan Education/Outreach, Animal Rights Education/Outreach, eventdescription: As populations and incomes rise throughout the world, more and more environmental scientists and economists are asking how the world will support its projected population of 9.5 billion people by 2050 and how governments can meet the climate change goals they committed to in the Paris Agreement. Venture capital firms, entrepreneurs, and major corporations are rising to the challenge, innovating and marketing plant and cultured alternatives to meat, dairy, and eggs that are cleaner, safer, and more sustainable.

In this talk, The Good Food Institute’s Bruce Friedrich will discuss why animal protein alternatives are gaining popularity with the biggest tech investors in Silicon Valley, including Bill Gates, Biz Stone, and Sergey Brin; how slaughter-free meat grown in a brewery will change how the world eats; and, why the future of protein is directly linked to the future of the planet itself.

Free food from HipCityVeg will be served. To guarantee your place at this exciting event, please sign up for EventBrite ticket. The event will be held in the Hall of Flags room in Houston Hall, University of Pennsylvania., linktoeventpageex.facebookmeetupeventbrite: https://www.facebook.com/events/343527096045122/, eventcontactinfo: pennanimaladvocacy@gmail.com, id: 0, start: 4/19/2017 17:00:00, end: 4/19/2017 17:00:01, url: https://www.facebook.com/events/343527096045122/

gsx$eventdescription.$t:
As populations and incomes rise throughout the world, more and more environmental scientists and economists are asking how the world will support its projected population of 9.5 billion people by 2050 and how governments can meet the climate change goals they committed to in the Paris Agreement. Venture capital firms, entrepreneurs, and major corporations are rising to the challenge, innovating and marketing plant and cultured alternatives to meat, dairy, and eggs that are cleaner, safer, and more sustainable.

In this talk, The Good Food Institute’s Bruce Friedrich will discuss why animal protein alternatives are gaining popularity with the biggest tech investors in Silicon Valley, including Bill Gates, Biz Stone, and Sergey Brin; how slaughter-free meat grown in a brewery will change how the world eats; and, why the future of protein is directly linked to the future of the planet itself.

Free food from HipCityVeg will be served. To guarantee your place at this exciting event, please sign up for EventBrite ticket. The event will be held in the Hall of Flags room in Houston Hall, University of Pennsylvania.

titleofevent: From the Warsaw Ghetto to a Life of Compassion, hostorganizationoryourname: Jewish Veg, date: 4/26/2017, starttime: 6:30:00 PM, endtime: 9:00:00 PM, location: The Gershman Y - 401 S Broad St, Philadelphia, PA 19147, typeofevent: Animal Rights Education/Outreach, eventdescription: Join us for an unforgettable evening as we welcome Holocaust survivor and legendary vegan leader Alex Hershaft to Philadelphia. Hear him share his dramatic and inspiring journey from the Warsaw Ghetto to a lifetime of compassion. This is the only opportunity to experience his stirring presentation in Philadelphia.

All proceeds from this event benefit Jewish Veg, a nonprofit organization dedicated to encouraging and helping people to adopt plant-based diets, in accordance with the highest ideals of Judaism.

Delicious vegan food by Birchtree Catering will be served.

Early Bird Discount: $18 per person!
